<br>
<br>
blademasters received 2 new abilities in this latest patch - Flurry and Advanced Evade.<br>
<br>
It is a little too soon to judge the effectiveness of these new abilities, they only recently hit the Live Servers. The general reception of these new skills was lukewarm at best, considering these are not exactly things we have been asking for.<br>
<br>
On average, Flurry adds about 100-150 Damage with a spec of 45 in Celtic Dual, the most common level to which CD is specced. This is equivilant to 1-2 additional swings every 2 minutes.<br>
<br>
<br>
Advanced evade is the ability to evage a target from every direction. While this is a useful skill, most blademasters agree that more defense was not something that was desired.<br>
<br>
We still suffer from a lack of front-load damage versus tanks from other realms, as well as our own. We will outdamage an opponent over time, however most RvR fights don't last long enough for us to do that kind of damage.<br>
<br>
I still feel that we should receive style damage on both swings, when both weapons swing with Celtic Dual. This would really help us a lot with being able to push out the kind of damage our class implies we should have.<br>
<br>
<br>
Unresolved issues:<br>
<br>
Styles/Ways to improve the CD line:<br>
<br>
There is still no &quot;detaunt&quot; style in Celtic Dual. There are curently 2 styles that chain off of the level 8 style, Snow Shower. Taking one of them and turning it into an anytime Detaunt would be a good idea.<br>
<br>
Perhaps reworking the Tornado-Meteor Shower-Twin Star Chain to have Medium Duration Bleed and a Long Duration Stun for the 2nd and 3rd parts of the chain would make this a more desireable chain to use. 3-style chains are rather difficult to get off, but less so for classes that use fast weapons, such as our own.<br>
<br>
There is still a problem with the damage scaling of our styles, the successive styles in the chains do not seem to scale up accordingly, particularly with our most-often used chain, Hurricane-Solar Flare.<br>
<br>
Off-Hand Weapons<br>
<br>
This has become a more pressing issue since the changes to the armor tables. Blunt is now a much more desireable weapon to spec in for Hibernia.<br>
<br>
There are currently no off-hand useable weapons for Piercing and Blunt that do above 15.3 DPS. This really needs to be addressed, as it has been something that blademasters have <br>
been asking for for a long time, and puts us at a disadvantage when compared to Blades users.<br>
<br>
Summary<br>
<br>
The blademaster is still the rock-bottom of class from an RvR standpoint. We have our niche in PvE, and do well there, but DAoC is an RvR game, and something needs to be done <br>
to level the playing field. <br>
<br>
We do not need more buttons or special abilities. We just want more damage, at the expense of our inferior defense.<br>
